{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect NR measurement processing in rrc_eNB_process_MeasurementReport\n\n### Summary\nThe `rrc_eNB_process_MeasurementReport` function in the LTE RRC eNB implementation had incorrect field access when processing NR measurement reports for NSA mode. The bug caused the target gNB PCI to be set incorrectly during EN-DC addition requests, leading to handover failures when attempting to add an NR secondary node.\n\nSpecifically, the function was accessing EUTRA measurement fields instead of NR measurement fields when extracting the target gNB PCI, and then overwriting it with a hardcoded value of 0.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_eNB.c`: \n  - Fixed NR measurement field access to correctly use `measResultNeighCellListNR_r15` instead of `measResultListEUTRA`\n  - Removed incorrect overwrite of `target_physCellId` with 0\n  - Corrected memory allocation size for NR measurement RS index list elements\n\n"
}